President Obama and Attorney General Holder met with a group of mayors to discuss strategies to reduce youth violence. The President emphasized that government cannot solve the issue alone and that everyone has a responsibility to create safe communities. He praised the mayors for their efforts and asked for their input on effective methods. The President also promised to take action on gun violence through executive measures and urged Congress to pass reforms such as expanding background checks and cracking down on gun trafficking. The meeting included mayors from various cities across the country.